      "site_admin": false
    },
    "created_at": "2016-10-27T16:51:16Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-10-27T16:51:16Z",
    "body": "> https://github.com/parro-it/electron-localshortcut\n\nAlthough that works, I wouldn't recommend using it.  Hacking around the `globalShortcut` module to make it become local has side effects and other issues.\n\nIf you want to do keyboard shortcuts for a BrowserWindow just use the `keyup` and `keydown` event listeners on the `window` object inside the renderer process.  I.e. \n\n``` js\nwindow.addEventListener('keyup', doThingOnKeyUp, true);\n```\n\nNote the third parameter true which means the listener will **always** receive key presses before other listeners so they can't have `stopPropagation()` called on them.\n"
  },
